\ul\b Product Requirements\par
\pard{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf4\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-270\li450\ulnone\b0 Version 5.5 or later of the WeatherLink software for Windows (including version 5.5V)\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Windows 98 or later, or Windows 95 with version 4 oe later of Internet Explorer\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Internet connection with access to an SMTP mail server required for e-mail functions\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Cell phone or pager text messaging functions require an e-mail address provided by your service provider.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Phone alerts require a modem and a normal telephone line to send the alerts. A second phone line is required to receive them\par
\pard\par
\ul\b E-mail/Phone Alert Module Version 1.0 Features\par
\pard{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf4\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-270\li450\ulnone\b0 Generates e-mail on either (or both) a fixed schedule, or when user selected alarm conditions occur.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}There are two e-mail formats available: a Standard format for normal usage and a Text Messaging format for use with cell phones and alphanumeric pagers with e-mail capabilities.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}The Standard format lists all alarms that are active, any sensors configured for the station that has missing data, plus a snapshot of the current weather conditions in a format similar to the Summary window.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}The Text Messaging format shows the same data except that the text is abbreviated and you can select exactly which feilds to include so that the most important information can be included in the limited message length available.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Alarms can be set for 49 different sensor conditions (e.g. High Outside Temp, Low Outside Temp, etc.).\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Two Combination Alarms are available to signal any combination of sensor conditions. (For example: Outside Temperature >= 90 F AND Outside Humidity >= 80 %.)\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Alarm notifications include the name of the alarm, the current value, and the threshold value that triggers the alarm.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Telephone alerts use a standard modem on the PC to place a phone call if an alarm condition occurs and generates a user defined set of "dial tone patterns" to communicate which alarm condition triggered the phone call. \par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Adds the following menu items:\par
\pard{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf4\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-270\li990 Setup: Setup Email Alerts...\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Setup: Setup Telephone Alerts...\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Help: Email/Phone Alert Help...\par
\pard\li180\par
\pard\ul\b Known Bugs\par
\pard{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf4\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-270\li450\ulnone\b0 Using an outgoing e-mail virus scanning program (such as Norton Anti-Virus) with a dialup internet connection may cause problems when sending e-mail. To work around this problem, either disable out going e-mail scanning, select the "Stay Connected all the Time" option in the Internet Connection Settings, or establish your dial up internet connection outside of WeatherLink before you send an e-mail.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}The included help file is incomplete. A complete help file will be available on our web site (www.davisnet.com) once it is ready.\par
\pard\li180\par
